<paragraph base="F4304338" id="IFRS07_44A"><paranum>44A</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 7"/><data name="paranum" value="44A"/></prolog><body><p id="IFRS07_P0816"><xref base="F4916604" href="../ias01/IAS01_TOC.dita#IAS01_TOC0001" id="IFRS07_X0718">IAS 1 (as revised in 2007)</xref> amended the terminology used throughout IFRSs. In addition it amended <xref base="F19328016" href="IFRS07_20.dita#IFRS07_20/IFRS07_20_V2" id="IFRS07_X0719">paragraphs 20</xref>, <xref base="F4916606" href="IFRS07_21.dita#IFRS07_21" id="IFRS07_X0720">21</xref>, <ph>23(c) and (d)</ph>, <xref base="F16458846" href="IFRS07_27-27B_DELETED.dita#IFRS07_27-27B" id="IFRS07_X0722">27(c)</xref> and <xref base="F19328017" href="IFRS07_B5.dita#IFRS07_B5/IFRS07_B5_V3" id="IFRS07_X0723">B5 of Appendix B</xref>. An entity shall apply those amendments for annual periods beginning on or after 1 January 2009. If an entity applies <xref base="F16458905" href="../ias01/IAS01_TOC.dita#IAS01_TOC0001" id="IFRS07_X0724">IAS 1</xref> (revised 2007) for an earlier period, the amendments shall be applied for that earlier period.</p></body></paragraph>